The paper discusses digital evolution and artificial life, which are subfields of artificial intelligence and robotics. The anecdotes collected in the paper are related to the surprising outcomes and adaptations that arise from evolutionary computation, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the creativity of digital organisms, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper touches on the broader implications of evolutionary surprises, which could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
